Trixxie Carissa — Tech Stack

Runtime

Python 3.14, fully async (asyncio)
Single process — Discord bot, SL bridge, and memory consolidation run concurrently via asyncio.gather()
AI / LLM

Anthropic Claude (claude-sonnet-4-6) via AsyncAnthropic SDK
Ollama (local models) as an alternative via openai.AsyncOpenAI pointed at the Ollama /v1 endpoint
Prompt caching (anthropic-beta: prompt-caching-2024-07-31) on the static system prompt block
Web Framework

FastAPI + Uvicorn — SL HTTP bridge, setup wizard, debug page, all served on one port (default 8080)
Platform Interfaces

discord.py — Discord bot
LSL (Linden Scripting Language, Mono compiler) — HUD script worn in Second Life
Cool VL Viewer Lua — native IM loop in the Cool VL Viewer (no /42 channel required)
Storage

Plain JSON files on disk (data/memory/, data/notes/) — no database
Per-(user, channel) asyncio.Lock for write serialization
Frontend (Setup Wizard & Debug)

Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS — no framework, no build step
SSE (Server-Sent Events) for live log streaming in the debug panel
Config

.env file loaded at startup via python-dotenv
data/agent_config.json for persona/tools (hot-reloaded after wizard save)
Tunnel

cloudflared to expose the local bridge to SL/OpenSim servers (free tunnel or named)